                                                                                                               Free bus ride 
                            
	New Delhi, Aug. 3 (PTI): Women will be allowed to travel free in DTC and low-floor buses on the occasion of Raksha Bandhan on August 5.        
	Delhi chief minister Sheila Dikshit said the decision had been taken to make it easier for women to visit their brothers. They would be allowed free rides in all DTC ordinary buses and green low-floor buses till 5pm on that day, Dikshit said.                                                                                                                                                                            
